               <p>BIRKHEAD HITCHCOCK sworn.</p>
               <p>On the 4th of February, I was in a room at the further end of my shop, I saw the prisoner pass and repass the shop two or three times, and I saw him come by the bulk of my window, slip off a bundle, put it under his arm, and walk away; mine is an open window, I ran after him immediately, and seized him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17850223-88-person925">
                  THOMAS
                   ROGERS
               <interp inst="t17850223-88-person925" type="surname" value="ROGERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850223-88-person925" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17850223-88-person925" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw the prisoner take the cloth.</p>
               <p>- REYNOLDS sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw the prosecutor follow a person and collar him just by my door, I saw the bundle taken from him and given to another man; I sent my young man home with him, to assist him.</p>
               <p>(The things deposed to.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I had been to Tower-wharf to know when the Ramsgate boy was going; I saw this property lay at a little distance from the door, and the prosecutor came and said it was his.</p>


               <p>
                  <rs id="t17850223-88-verdict413" type="verdictDescription">
